                    <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><font color="#990000">&bull;</font></font> <A 
href="http://usinfo.state.gov/journals/itdhr/1007/ijde/usefulness.htm">Has the Electoral College Outlived Its Usefulness?</A> Oct., 2007 (eJournal USA: The Long Campaign)<font color="#990000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><b><br>
                    </b></font></p>
                </TD>
                <TD vAlign=top width="52%"><p> 
                    <span class="style41"><font color="#990000" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">Election Laws</font></span> </p>
                  <p class="style18"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><font color="#990000">&bull;</font></font> <A 
href="http://www.nass.org/index.php?option=com_docman&amp;task=doc_download&amp;gid=46">Early Voting and Absentee Ballot Laws</A> (NASS) - 2007 comparison of state election laws on the subject<br>  
                      <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><font color="#990000">&bull;</font></font> <A href="http://www.fec.gov/hava/hava.htm">Help America Vote Act</A> - Passed in 2002 to assist states in migrating from punch card systems, additional standardization provisions<br>
                      <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><font color="#990000">&bull;</font></font> <A 
href="http://www.nass.org/index.php?option=com_docman&amp;task=doc_download&amp;gid=52">Provisional Voting Laws</A> - table listing states and a brief description of their provisional voting laws, compiled by the National Association of Secretaries of State in 2004<br>
                      <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><font color="#990000">&bull;</font></font> <A 
href="http://nass.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;task=blogcategory&amp;id=33&amp;Itemid=187">State Election Laws and Administrative Issues</A> (National Association of Secretaries of State) - Tables compare election laws on absentee voting and vote counting, early voting, provisional ballots, same day registration, student residency requirements<br>
                      <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1"><font color="#990000">&bull;</font></font> <A 
href="http://www.nass.org/index.php?option=com_docman&amp;task=doc_download&amp;gid=54">Residency Requirements for College Students</A> (NASS) - Comparative state laws based on survey </p>
